Dragon Dodger

🐲 🌈 🌈 🐲

What is this?
This is a tiny, friendly game project built with the Godot Engine. The goal is to dodge obstacles along a rainbow path.

What you need (no coding background required)
1) Godot Engine 4.x (free). Download it from the official Godot website.
2) This project folder on your computer.

How to open and run the game
1) Open Godot.
2) Click Import.
3) Select the godot folder inside this project.
4) Open the project.
5) Press the Play button (▶) to run Level 1.

What you’ll see right now
- A rainbow arc (the track)
- A few thorn and swirl obstacles (visual placeholders)
- A basic scene setup ready for movement logic

For developers (optional)
This repo also includes a simple Python CLI scaffold managed by Poetry. It is not required to run the Godot project.

Project layout
- godot: Godot project files and scenes
- dragon_dodger: Python package for the CLI entrypoint
- requirements.md: Game design notes and ideas